{
  "stem": "18778.4",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 491.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And, and we were stopped by air raids several times during the night.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The train stopped.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The rumor was that the men from the internment camps who were scheduled to board with us were in a sealed car at the end of the train, again, under Scotland Yard guard.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We got to Glasgow, and they brought us to the ship.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The SS Cameronia was the name of the ship-- C-A-M-E-R-O-N-I-A.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Who wasn't there was my father and the other men who were expected.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We waited and we waited.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I think we were supposed to sail toward evening, and finally, maybe an hour before sailing time, the men came on board.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "What had happened was that they put them on another ship to go to Australia.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "You see, the British had shipped many young single men of, of military age who were among those internees-- had shipped them off to Australia and New Zealand.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And somebody thought that this batch of men were also supposed to be destined, and I think they, they mutinied.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And so finally, they appeared on the ship, and that was quite a reunion.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "The ship left.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We had on board with us the entire-- there was only two class-- second class and third class, in this case.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Second class was entirely British children who were being sent to this hemisphere for the duration, to the States and to Canada.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And we had a convoy that crossed, crossed with us.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Luckily, we made it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "We were pursued by German submarines.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "The ships before and after us were, were torpedoed.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "We got through, luckily.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And so we arrived in New York on September 10, 1940.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "We hadn't seen a city in lights for years because even before-- even when we still lived in Germany, there were demi-blackouts.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
